# graphic-design / Cairo (pycairo / cairosvg)

Cairo is a mature C 2D vector graphics library driven from Python two ways: pycairo (imperative — draw paths/text/gradients to a Surface, then write PNG/SVG/PDF) and CairoSVG (declarative — transcode an existing SVG to PNG/PDF/PS). Output is deterministic and fully headless: no display server needed. This wrapper renders an image (PNG) deliverable; the source script or SVG is the version-controllable artifact.

controls do
