## Required reading
- pycairo official docs (pygobject / Christoph Reiter, LGPL-2.1/MPL-1.1) — https://pycairo.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
- CairoSVG official docs (Kozea / CourtBouillon, LGPL-3.0-or-later) — https://cairosvg.org/documentation/
- cairo graphics library docs (cairographics.org, LGPL-2.1/MPL-1.1) — https://www.cairographics.org/documentation/
- No official Anthropic/Claude skill — drive the documented Python APIs directly.

## Render
```bash
# native dep first (most common build failure is missing system cairo/FFI)
brew install cairo pkg-config libffi
pip install pycairo CairoSVG

# pycairo (imperative): the .py is the source, the .png is the deliverable
python3 draw.py            # surface.write_to_png('out.png')

# cairosvg (declarative): author/generate the .svg, then transcode
cairosvg in.svg -o out.png
```

## Failure modes
- Missing system cairo / FFI headers at wheel build → `pip install pycairo` fails. Run `brew install cairo pkg-config libffi` first.
- Text glyphs vary across machines (font-dependent). Pin fonts via fontconfig / bundle a `.ttf` and `fc-cache` for reproducible output.
- pycairo raises on bad surface status — check exceptions; exit nonzero on cairo error.
- CairoSVG only handles SVG 1.1; exotic SVG2 features may not render faithfully.
